22
00:00:02.802 --> 00:00:04.871
You understand to claim a dragon

23
00:00:04.971 --> 00:00:07.540
you must also be
prepared to die.

24
00:00:07.640 --> 00:00:09.843
(Dragon screeches)

25
00:00:09.976 --> 00:00:11.745
(Flames raging)

26
00:00:11.978 --> 00:00:16.915
♪

27
00:00:16.916 --> 00:00:20.387
It was a reckless thought that
an ancicent Valyrian beast

28
00:00:20.487 --> 00:00:21.807
would suffer a
Darklyn to ride it.

29
00:00:21.988 --> 00:00:23.922
Surely he was not
the only possibility.

30
00:00:23.923 --> 00:00:25.290
Aemond: I must see my brother.

31
00:00:25.291 --> 00:00:26.992
What do you remember?

32
00:00:26.993 --> 00:00:28.260
(Aegon groaning)

33
00:00:28.261 --> 00:00:30.429
I remember nothing.

34
00:00:30.430 --> 00:00:32.232
♪

35
00:00:32.332 --> 00:00:33.599
(People clamoring)

36
00:00:33.600 --> 00:00:35.167
The smallfolk of King's
Landing are listening.

37
00:00:35.168 --> 00:00:36.703
They are hungry.

38
00:00:36.836 --> 00:00:38.270
Our gift is sent.

39
00:00:38.271 --> 00:00:41.041
♪

40
00:00:41.174 --> 00:00:43.009
(People shouting)

41
00:00:43.176 --> 00:00:44.411
Give it to me!

42
00:00:44.511 --> 00:00:47.213
Your Graces. we must leave.

43
00:00:47.347 --> 00:00:48.681
(People shouting)

44
00:00:48.848 --> 00:00:50.283
It's the Queen of Fishes!

45
00:00:50.517 --> 00:00:52.285
Man: Long Live Queen Rhaenyra!

46
00:00:52.519 --> 00:00:54.286
♪

47
00:00:54.287 --> 00:00:56.332
If you have any council for
dealing with the River Lords

48
00:00:56.356 --> 00:00:57.489
I'd be glad of it.

49
00:00:57.490 --> 00:00:59.625
Grover Tully is
their Lord Paramount.

50
00:00:59.626 --> 00:01:02.795
Without him they will never
raise their banners as one.

51
00:01:02.796 --> 00:01:04.197
♪

52
00:01:04.364 --> 00:01:06.342
This is Oscar Tully. grandson
to Grover Tully. he is heir to

53
00:01:06.366 --> 00:01:09.535
Riverrun and the future Lord
Paramount of the Riverlands.

54
00:01:09.536 --> 00:01:12.605
Houses Bracken and Blackwood
have long-detested one-another.

55
00:01:12.705 --> 00:01:14.374
(Dragon screeches)

56
00:01:14.541 --> 00:01:16.476
We have fought them
for an age and more.

57
00:01:16.709 --> 00:01:19.511
There are things the crown
itself must not be seen to do.

58
00:01:19.512 --> 00:01:21.648
Show them your worst.

59
00:01:21.881 --> 00:01:23.650
I am your servant. Your Grace.

60
00:01:23.883 --> 00:01:25.151
♪

61
00:01:25.385 --> 00:01:27.019
Man: There were
works of barbarity.

62
00:01:27.020 --> 00:01:30.656
Dragon or no. we shall not
raise our banners for a tyrant.

63
00:01:30.657 --> 00:01:33.358
Your Grace. Lord Grover is dead.

64
00:01:33.359 --> 00:01:36.995
Young Oscar Tully is now Lord
Paramount of the Riverlands.

65
00:01:36.996 --> 00:01:40.333
When I take King's Landing
Rhaenyra is welcome

66
00:01:40.567 --> 00:01:42.935
to join me there and take
her place by my side.

67
00:01:42.936 --> 00:01:45.972
(Dynamic music)

68
00:01:46.072 --> 00:01:47.707
There is a large
dragon in the Vale.

69
00:01:47.907 --> 00:01:49.809
Large. but alas. wild.

70
00:01:49.909 --> 00:01:52.112
You saved his life. brother.

71
00:01:52.245 --> 00:01:53.965
Do you never think about
what could be ours.

72
00:01:54.080 --> 00:01:56.683
(Seasmoke screeching)

73
00:01:56.916 --> 00:01:59.886
♪

74
00:02:00.086 --> 00:02:01.855
Your Grace.

75
00:02:02.088 --> 00:02:04.891
the dragon Seasmoke has been
seen flying over Spice Town.

76
00:02:05.091 --> 00:02:06.692
From what we have
heard he has a rider.

77
00:02:06.693 --> 00:02:09.761
♪

78
00:02:09.762 --> 00:02:11.530
(Syrax roars)

79
00:02:11.531 --> 00:02:12.932
♪

80
00:02:20.874 --> 00:02:24.010
{\an8}(epic theme playing)

81
00:02:26.000 --> 00:02:32.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

82
00:03:09.155 --> 00:03:11.224
{\an8}♪

83
00:04:04.577 --> 00:04:06.913
(theme fades out)

84
00:04:11.517 --> 00:04:13.620
{\an8}(Syrax roars)

85
00:04:14.721 --> 00:04:16.823
{\an8}(Seasmoke roars)

86
00:04:18.758 --> 00:04:21.928
(dragons grumbling. calling)

87
00:04:46.052 --> 00:04:52.157
(shouts) You stand before the
Queen of the Seven Kingdoms...

88
00:04:52.158 --> 00:04:55.361
with a dragon of
House Targaryen!

89
00:04:56.529 --> 00:04:58.764
(shouts) I had no
design upon it!

90
00:04:58.765 --> 00:05:00.900
What do you want?!

91
00:05:01.634 --> 00:05:04.937
Addam of Hull: To learn
the ways of dragonriders.

92
00:05:06.239 --> 00:05:08.374
And to serve my queen!

93
00:05:10.009 --> 00:05:12.144
Your Grace!

94
00:05:12.145 --> 00:05:14.347
(dragons grumbling)

95
00:05:24.023 --> 00:05:26.159
(dragons howling)

96
00:05:30.730 --> 00:05:32.832
(Seasmoke roars)

97
00:05:39.439 --> 00:05:41.673
You kneel quickly...

98
00:05:41.674 --> 00:05:44.277
for a man so suddenly elevated.

99
00:05:44.844 --> 00:05:48.747
This dragon came to
me. not I to him.

100
00:05:48.748 --> 00:05:50.782
(Seasmoke howls)

101
00:05:50.783 --> 00:05:54.986
I have sweated blood in
service of House Velaryon.

102
00:05:54.987 --> 00:05:57.489
I may appear lowborn...

103
00:05:57.490 --> 00:06:00.593
but I know much and
more of service!

104
00:06:02.028 --> 00:06:04.162
And if the gods call
me to greater things.

105
00:06:04.163 --> 00:06:05.998
who am I to refuse them?

106
00:06:15.508 --> 00:06:16.776
Stand.

107
00:06:25.051 --> 00:06:26.651
What is your parentage?

108
00:06:26.652 --> 00:06:29.021
My mother was a shipwright.

109
00:06:30.089 --> 00:06:31.791
My father is...

110
00:06:32.892 --> 00:06:34.394
no one of consequence.

111
00:06:35.027 --> 00:06:37.963
Your ancestors. any
of House Targaryen?

112
00:06:37.964 --> 00:06:41.567
We're not the sort of family
to keep annals. Your Grace.

113
00:06:43.703 --> 00:06:45.438
What is your name?

114
00:06:45.671 --> 00:06:47.974
Addam... of Hull.

115
00:06:51.577 --> 00:06:53.713
(Seasmoke grumbling)

116
00:06:56.482 --> 00:06:58.818
You have done something...

117
00:07:00.086 --> 00:07:02.221
I feared impossible...

118
00:07:03.689 --> 00:07:05.792
Addam of Hull.

119
00:07:10.363 --> 00:07:12.298
I am glad of it.

120
00:07:13.332 --> 00:07:16.334
(light music playing)

121
00:07:16.335 --> 00:07:18.738
Do you think you can
get him to Dragonstone?

122
00:07:21.641 --> 00:07:23.409
I can try.

123
00:07:27.480 --> 00:07:29.314
(music fades out)

124
00:07:29.315 --> 00:07:31.283
Alicent Hightower:
All my life...

125
00:07:31.284 --> 00:07:35.655
I have endeavored to serve
both my house and the realm.

126
00:07:37.290 --> 00:07:39.192
And somehow none of it matters.

127
00:07:41.327 --> 00:07:43.296
We are cast aside.

128
00:07:45.198 --> 00:07:46.699
Or hated.

129
00:07:49.769 --> 00:07:52.237
You'll have a scar...

130
00:07:52.238 --> 00:07:55.707
but... (inhales) it
will be easily hidden.

131
00:07:55.708 --> 00:07:57.877
(nearby scritching)

132
00:08:00.880 --> 00:08:02.714
Nothing is clean here.

133
00:08:02.715 --> 00:08:04.884
(rat squeaking)

134
00:08:10.523 --> 00:08:12.457
(distant chatter)

135
00:08:12.458 --> 00:08:14.894
I wish to go out. Ser Rickard.

136
00:08:15.328 --> 00:08:16.829
Rickard Thorne: Out?

137
00:08:17.330 --> 00:08:18.897
To the Kingswood. I think.

138
00:08:18.898 --> 00:08:20.298
Then I'll have the
stewards prepare

139
00:08:20.299 --> 00:08:22.368
- a retinue.
- No retinue.

140
00:08:23.369 --> 00:08:25.303
- Then your handmaidens...
- No handmaidens.

141
00:08:25.304 --> 00:08:28.140
- (birds chirping)
- Just you.

142
00:08:34.914 --> 00:08:37.382
(indistinct chatter)

143
00:08:37.383 --> 00:08:41.419
Jasper "Ironrod" Wylde: What are
they for? The block or the crow cage?

144
00:08:41.420 --> 00:08:43.922
Larys Strong: The Wall.

145
00:08:43.923 --> 00:08:45.957
The prince regent is merciful.

146
00:08:45.958 --> 00:08:47.059
Hm.

147
00:08:48.794 --> 00:08:51.396
Well. they started a riot.

148
00:08:51.397 --> 00:08:54.500
Justice is served. I suppose.

149
00:08:56.102 --> 00:08:58.204
(horse neighs)

150
00:09:01.741 --> 00:09:05.411
I have received word of a
matter of great importance.

151
00:09:06.279 --> 00:09:09.415
Rumor of a sighting of
the dragon Seasmoke...

152
00:09:10.583 --> 00:09:12.285
with a rider.

153
00:09:13.252 --> 00:09:15.320
A fine piece of intelligence.

154
00:09:15.321 --> 00:09:19.090
and now you seek favor by
delivering it to Prince Aemond.

155
00:09:19.091 --> 00:09:23.194
Actually. I thought I might
seek your advice. Lord Larys.

156
00:09:23.195 --> 00:09:25.231
Whispers being your province.

157
00:09:25.665 --> 00:09:29.569
Guard: Kneel before the Prince
Regent Aemond Targaryen!

158
00:09:30.036 --> 00:09:32.003
Oh. but this is your whisper.

159
00:09:32.004 --> 00:09:34.673
Lord Jasper. not mine.

160
00:09:34.674 --> 00:09:37.576
But if you consider
it valuable...

161
00:09:37.577 --> 00:09:39.744
perhaps you could deliver it

162
00:09:39.745 --> 00:09:42.080
and find favor with
Aemond yourself.

163
00:09:42.081 --> 00:09:44.683
Aemond Targaryen: You will forsake
your white cloaks for black.

164
00:09:44.684 --> 00:09:47.519
Serve out your days at The Wall.

165
00:09:47.520 --> 00:09:49.554
Larys: Who is this rider?

166
00:09:49.555 --> 00:09:52.457
Ironrod: That is less clear.

167
00:09:52.458 --> 00:09:54.893
but it must surely
be the Lady Rhaena.

168
00:09:54.894 --> 00:09:56.761
She has wanted for a
dragon all her life.

169
00:09:56.762 --> 00:09:58.363
Indeed. but she tried already

170
00:09:58.364 --> 00:09:59.564
when she was four and ten.

171
00:09:59.565 --> 00:10:01.866
The beast Seasmoke very
nearly devoured her.

172
00:10:01.867 --> 00:10:03.336
Who else?

173
00:10:04.604 --> 00:10:07.439
Yes. it is a shallow pool.

174
00:10:07.440 --> 00:10:09.341
Where did you hear it?

175
00:10:09.342 --> 00:10:10.676
My squire.

176
00:10:12.244 --> 00:10:14.713
He heard it from a stablehand.

177
00:10:14.714 --> 00:10:18.283
who heard it from his
father. a fisherman.

178
00:10:18.284 --> 00:10:20.820
whose shipmate claims he saw it.

179
00:10:21.988 --> 00:10:23.022
Oh.

180
00:10:26.392 --> 00:10:28.727
You are. of course.
welcome to bring this news

181
00:10:28.728 --> 00:10:31.464
to the prince regent. but. um...

182
00:10:32.131 --> 00:10:36.102
perhaps this is one of those
whispers best left to the wind.

183
00:10:40.339 --> 00:10:42.441
(prisoners struggling)

184
00:10:43.209 --> 00:10:45.110
(Ironrod clears throat)

185
00:10:45.111 --> 00:10:48.781
- (tense music playing)
- (horse neighs)

186
00:10:58.090 --> 00:11:00.091
(dragons calling)

187
00:11:00.092 --> 00:11:02.228
♪

188
00:11:14.040 --> 00:11:16.207
(music fades out)

189
00:11:16.208 --> 00:11:18.076
The queen is unharmed.

190
00:11:18.077 --> 00:11:21.012
Corlys Velaryon: What of the
rider? Do we know who he is?

191
00:11:21.013 --> 00:11:22.847
He appears to be a shipwright

192
00:11:22.848 --> 00:11:24.749
in your employ. Lord Hand.

193
00:11:24.750 --> 00:11:26.317
Bartimos Celtigar: A commoner?

194
00:11:26.318 --> 00:11:28.853
With respect to your
workers. Lord Corlys.

195
00:11:28.854 --> 00:11:32.991
the lowborn cannot go
around seizing dragons.

196
00:11:32.992 --> 00:11:34.959
Has the thief been secured?

197
00:11:34.960 --> 00:11:38.430
Her Grace has commanded that
he remain here as a guest.

198
00:11:38.431 --> 00:11:40.031
She wishes him to be instructed

199
00:11:40.032 --> 00:11:42.400
in the art of dragonriding.

200
00:11:42.401 --> 00:11:45.403
and that I should teach
him some High Valyrian.

201
00:11:45.404 --> 00:11:47.605
Bartimos: We know
nothing about this man.

202
00:11:47.606 --> 00:11:49.407
save that he is lowborn.

203
00:11:49.408 --> 00:11:51.844
What say you. Lord Hand?

204
00:11:53.312 --> 00:11:55.147
We will await the
queen's accounting...

205
00:11:56.048 --> 00:11:59.085
- before passing judgment.
- (Bartimos sighs)

206
00:12:01.387 --> 00:12:02.955
Where is the queen?

207
00:12:04.724 --> 00:12:07.359
Her Grace sends word she
will not be attending.

208
00:12:11.630 --> 00:12:14.400
Mysaria: So he serves
you and not himself.

209
00:12:14.667 --> 00:12:17.235
- That is lucky.
- Lucky?

210
00:12:17.236 --> 00:12:19.437
Or somehow ordained?

211
00:12:19.438 --> 00:12:21.106
Seasmoke chose him.

212
00:12:21.107 --> 00:12:24.509
He surely has Targaryen
blood in him somewhere.

213
00:12:24.510 --> 00:12:25.810
The dragon must sense it.

214
00:12:25.811 --> 00:12:26.945
There will be others.

215
00:12:26.946 --> 00:12:27.946
We will find riders

216
00:12:27.947 --> 00:12:29.147
for Vermithor and Silverwing.

217
00:12:29.148 --> 00:12:30.649
You trust this man?

218
00:12:31.417 --> 00:12:32.884
What choice do I have?

219
00:12:32.885 --> 00:12:34.252
He has a dragon.

220
00:12:34.253 --> 00:12:35.754
Without him. I have only Syrax

221
00:12:35.755 --> 00:12:38.224
who may give Aemond
a second thought.

222
00:12:38.758 --> 00:12:40.760
The question is where to look.

223
00:12:41.193 --> 00:12:45.263
Targaryen blood was perhaps too
thin in Ser Steffon Darklyn.

224
00:12:45.264 --> 00:12:47.632
If I can find others
with a more direct line

225
00:12:47.633 --> 00:12:50.735
- of breeding.
- (Mysaria chuckles)

226
00:12:50.736 --> 00:12:52.905
Forgive me. Your Grace...

227
00:12:55.074 --> 00:12:59.578
but you are better served looking
under the sheets and in the woodpiles.

228
00:13:03.382 --> 00:13:05.150
I once worked in
a pleasure house

229
00:13:05.151 --> 00:13:09.454
where generations of Targaryen
princelings had their revels.

230
00:13:09.455 --> 00:13:13.091
There are four score of their
bastard progeny at least.

231
00:13:13.092 --> 00:13:14.759
that are known to me.

232
00:13:14.760 --> 00:13:16.861
There are sure to be more.

233
00:13:16.862 --> 00:13:18.897
Perhaps some here.
on Dragonstone.

234
00:13:18.898 --> 00:13:22.701
the misbegotten
offspring of your house.

235
00:13:32.411 --> 00:13:33.878
You speak of the lowborn.

236
00:13:33.879 --> 00:13:35.446
They are as like to serve you

237
00:13:35.447 --> 00:13:39.151
as highborn lords or
ladies. perhaps more.

238
00:13:41.420 --> 00:13:44.422
But in the highborn
houses there is...

239
00:13:44.423 --> 00:13:47.226
(inhales) an ancient fealty.

240
00:13:48.127 --> 00:13:49.361
There is honor.

241
00:13:50.029 --> 00:13:53.364
Your royal half-brothers.
Aegon and Aemond.

242
00:13:53.365 --> 00:13:59.437
whose blood is pure. who wage
war against you for your throne.

243
00:13:59.438 --> 00:14:01.207
are they bound by honor?

244
00:14:06.579 --> 00:14:10.315
A common shipwright
vows to serve you

245
00:14:10.316 --> 00:14:13.586
while your brothers
seek to destroy you.

246
00:14:15.087 --> 00:14:19.258
The order of things has
changed. Your Grace.

247
00:14:20.092 --> 00:14:22.061
Why not embrace it?

248
00:14:31.670 --> 00:14:34.672
For 20 years. the lords
of this realm levied...

249
00:14:34.673 --> 00:14:38.544
insults at my sons
behind my back.

250
00:14:46.051 --> 00:14:47.353
Well then.

251
00:14:48.454 --> 00:14:52.057
Let us raise an
army of bastards.

252
00:15:12.544 --> 00:15:15.281
- My lord.
- Corlys: "My lord"?

253
00:15:15.748 --> 00:15:18.150
How you have come
up in the world.

254
00:15:20.352 --> 00:15:22.420
I wish to ask for leave
to relinquish my part

255
00:15:22.421 --> 00:15:24.522
as a shipwright in your service.

256
00:15:24.523 --> 00:15:27.626
There are good men and strong
who can take my place...

257
00:15:32.464 --> 00:15:34.767
Your leave is granted.

258
00:15:46.679 --> 00:15:48.247
Well done.

259
00:15:51.483 --> 00:15:54.653
(intense music playing)

260
00:15:57.189 --> 00:15:59.291
(horses neigh)

261
00:16:05.664 --> 00:16:07.766
♪

262
00:16:14.773 --> 00:16:16.541
(knocks on door)

263
00:16:16.542 --> 00:16:19.110
Simon Strong: Lord Tully has
answered your summons and brought

264
00:16:19.111 --> 00:16:21.714
the Riverlords. my king.

265
00:16:26.685 --> 00:16:29.721
Daemon Targaryen: My condolences
on the passing of your grandsire

266
00:16:29.722 --> 00:16:32.724
but the crown congratulates you on your
ascension to the head of your house

267
00:16:32.725 --> 00:16:34.525
and Lord Paramount
in the Riverlands.

268
00:16:34.526 --> 00:16:35.961
Truly glorious. Well done.

269
00:16:36.862 --> 00:16:41.399
- I did nothing.
- Nevertheless. you are here. which is the important thing.

270
00:16:41.400 --> 00:16:43.234
You were quick enough
to dismiss me before.

271
00:16:43.235 --> 00:16:45.837
You were of no
significance to me then.

272
00:16:45.838 --> 00:16:47.172
Now...

273
00:16:49.742 --> 00:16:52.378
I shall have my great host.

274
00:16:53.212 --> 00:16:55.446
You have a decision to make.

275
00:16:55.447 --> 00:16:57.883
I presume it is clear to
you which is the right one.

276
00:16:58.650 --> 00:17:00.518
Oscar Tully: You'll
forgive me. Your Grace.

277
00:17:00.519 --> 00:17:02.587
I am green in this
sort of matter.

278
00:17:02.588 --> 00:17:06.458
as you so kindly point
out. but... (inhales)

279
00:17:07.359 --> 00:17:10.862
it does seem to me that you've
made rather a mess here.

280
00:17:10.863 --> 00:17:14.966
countenancing barbarities
in the queen's name.

281
00:17:14.967 --> 00:17:17.169
Whose side are you on?

282
00:17:19.004 --> 00:17:21.006
(deep breath)

283
00:17:21.507 --> 00:17:24.743
The Riverlands are
held together by oaths.

284
00:17:26.178 --> 00:17:30.049
House Tully swore an
oath to King Viserys.

285
00:17:31.683 --> 00:17:33.051
We recognize the authority

286
00:17:33.052 --> 00:17:35.621
of the named heir.
Queen Rhaenyra

287
00:17:36.055 --> 00:17:39.925
and your own... as
her king consort.

288
00:17:41.193 --> 00:17:42.461
Good.

289
00:17:43.662 --> 00:17:45.096
Then we shall go to
face your vassals

290
00:17:45.097 --> 00:17:46.531
and you will call
your banners to war.

291
00:17:46.532 --> 00:17:49.034
That might be
difficult. my king.

292
00:17:54.073 --> 00:17:55.374
Well...

293
00:17:56.642 --> 00:17:58.142
I was told they
would come to heel

294
00:17:58.143 --> 00:18:00.545
when House Tully
declared its allegiance.

295
00:18:00.546 --> 00:18:02.680
That may be the case.

296
00:18:02.681 --> 00:18:05.583
though it is yet to be seen
that they will heed my authority

297
00:18:05.584 --> 00:18:07.753
as young as it is.

298
00:18:09.188 --> 00:18:11.290
And there is another problem.

299
00:18:13.258 --> 00:18:14.959
They all hate you.

300
00:18:14.960 --> 00:18:18.429
(quiet. tense music playing)

301
00:18:18.430 --> 00:18:20.298
I don't need their love.

302
00:18:20.299 --> 00:18:22.400
I need their swords.

303
00:18:22.401 --> 00:18:24.436
(door opens)

304
00:18:24.837 --> 00:18:28.840
Your Grace. my lord.
The Riverlords await.

305
00:18:28.841 --> 00:18:31.477
I fear we cannot
delay them any longer.

306
00:18:37.983 --> 00:18:40.352
Daemon: Come
along. Lord Oscar.

307
00:18:44.089 --> 00:18:46.191
(music intensifies)

308
00:19:02.841 --> 00:19:05.344
In the deepest darkness
comes the dawn.

309
00:19:06.044 --> 00:19:07.345
A new lord.

310
00:19:07.346 --> 00:19:09.148
a new beginning.

311
00:19:10.082 --> 00:19:12.885
Let us put all the old
unpleasantness behind us.

312
00:19:18.824 --> 00:19:20.959
Be welcome. my lords...

313
00:19:21.894 --> 00:19:24.996
and you have my thanks
for answering my summons.

314
00:19:24.997 --> 00:19:27.665
I know I'm not the
man my grandsire was.

315
00:19:27.666 --> 00:19:32.637
but I hope to begin well.
and go on from there.

316
00:19:32.638 --> 00:19:35.807
Daemon: Well said.
One thing is clear...

317
00:19:36.441 --> 00:19:39.644
the Rivermen honor the old
ways and abide by tradition.

318
00:19:39.645 --> 00:19:41.679
Here. then. is tradition.

319
00:19:41.680 --> 00:19:43.147
Grover Tully is dead.

320
00:19:43.148 --> 00:19:45.149
Lord Oscar raised
up in his place.

321
00:19:45.150 --> 00:19:46.751
You have been summoned here

322
00:19:46.752 --> 00:19:48.653
to swear anew your
fealty to him.

323
00:19:48.654 --> 00:19:52.623
and as his bannermen.
answer his call.

324
00:19:52.624 --> 00:19:54.892
And what would that call be?

325
00:19:54.893 --> 00:19:57.061
In his wisdom. he has
pledged his house.

326
00:19:57.062 --> 00:19:58.896
and yours. to me.

327
00:19:58.897 --> 00:20:00.631
(Riverlords murmuring)

328
00:20:00.632 --> 00:20:04.101
Lord Piper: Lord Oscar. for
generations we have been guided

329
00:20:04.102 --> 00:20:06.205
by the judgment
of your forebears.

330
00:20:06.538 --> 00:20:10.041
Why should we now follow a
boy. younger than my own sons.

331
00:20:10.042 --> 00:20:11.409
when you will align with one

332
00:20:11.410 --> 00:20:13.744
who will desecrate the
innocent to reach his aims?

333
00:20:13.745 --> 00:20:15.179
(Riverlords murmuring)

334
00:20:15.180 --> 00:20:19.517
I did only what was
necessary. my lord.

335
00:20:19.518 --> 00:20:21.752
And I now deliver
to you the traitor

336
00:20:21.753 --> 00:20:23.955
Amos Bracken and his son.

337
00:20:23.956 --> 00:20:27.359
No more traitor to his land
than you. Willem Blackwood.

338
00:20:28.093 --> 00:20:30.628
I take to heart your
words. Lord Piper.

339
00:20:30.629 --> 00:20:33.865
and I agree. I-I-I am young.

340
00:20:34.499 --> 00:20:35.767
(sighs)

341
00:20:36.768 --> 00:20:40.004
And I have no love
for Daemon Targaryen.

342
00:20:40.005 --> 00:20:43.308
He has dishonored himself
and the crown with his...

343
00:20:44.276 --> 00:20:47.078
comportment here.

344
00:20:47.079 --> 00:20:51.048
Nevertheless. having so
little experience to guide me.

345
00:20:51.049 --> 00:20:54.919
my best course is to defer to
the oath my grandsire swore

346
00:20:54.920 --> 00:20:58.890
to King Viserys when he
named Rhaenyra his heir.

347
00:21:01.960 --> 00:21:05.363
I see no reason to
cast aside loyalty

348
00:21:05.364 --> 00:21:09.267
no matter how loathsome I may find
her representative the prince.

349
00:21:09.268 --> 00:21:10.602
King.

350
00:21:11.470 --> 00:21:13.472
Mind your tongue. boy.

351
00:21:14.806 --> 00:21:16.942
(Riverlords murmuring)

352
00:21:25.317 --> 00:21:27.853
Will you have our army or not?

353
00:21:38.330 --> 00:21:40.931
I am. in the end. a Riverman

354
00:21:40.932 --> 00:21:43.134
and the word of my house stands.

355
00:21:43.135 --> 00:21:46.037
even if certain people
are unworthy of it.

356
00:21:46.038 --> 00:21:48.807
(wind blowing)

357
00:21:49.641 --> 00:21:50.942
(sighs)

358
00:21:53.845 --> 00:21:56.381
Your Lord Oscar is bold.

359
00:21:57.616 --> 00:22:00.185
But he is perhaps not wrong.

360
00:22:00.952 --> 00:22:03.621
I may have been a
touch enthusiastic

361
00:22:03.622 --> 00:22:06.557
in pursuing my aims.

362
00:22:06.558 --> 00:22:09.960
But don't allow
my failings to...

363
00:22:09.961 --> 00:22:13.097
keep you from supporting
an upright man.

364
00:22:13.098 --> 00:22:15.966
Lady Mallister: Lord Oscar.
we honor the old ways.

365
00:22:15.967 --> 00:22:18.369
as Prince Daemon says

366
00:22:18.370 --> 00:22:21.939
- and the old ways call for justice to be done.
- riverlord: Yes!

367
00:22:21.940 --> 00:22:24.175
Justice has been done.

368
00:22:24.176 --> 00:22:28.680
They who bent the knee to the
usurper have been brought to heel.

369
00:22:29.414 --> 00:22:34.086
And now. we unite
before our liege lord...

370
00:22:35.787 --> 00:22:38.190
and our king consort.

371
00:22:52.137 --> 00:22:56.007
I accept you as my vassal.
Willem Blackwood...

372
00:23:03.115 --> 00:23:04.282
but...

373
00:23:05.751 --> 00:23:09.187
I am Lord Paramount
of all River Houses.

374
00:23:10.922 --> 00:23:12.556
And there is only one
answer for the crimes

375
00:23:12.557 --> 00:23:14.393
you visited upon your neighbors.

376
00:23:18.330 --> 00:23:22.400
I did only what His Grace
the king required of me.

377
00:23:22.401 --> 00:23:25.836
Oscar: It is true that he
made clear his base desires.

378
00:23:25.837 --> 00:23:29.374
but you did not have to
pursue such savagery.

379
00:23:30.409 --> 00:23:34.379
You did it... because
you wanted to.

380
00:23:34.613 --> 00:23:37.115
Our young lord speaks truly.

381
00:23:38.650 --> 00:23:41.319
- Seize him.
- (Riverlords murmuring)

382
00:23:42.154 --> 00:23:45.589
Willem Blackwood:
Don't fuckin' do this.

383
00:23:45.590 --> 00:23:48.927
Your Grace. command them.
I've only served you.

384
00:23:53.498 --> 00:23:55.533
- Command them.
- Oscar: If His Grace wishes

385
00:23:55.534 --> 00:23:57.968
to show contrition for his acts

386
00:23:57.969 --> 00:24:01.673
and to prove himself
deserving of our banners

387
00:24:02.441 --> 00:24:05.142
he must now rectify
his grievous error.

388
00:24:05.143 --> 00:24:07.746
Denounce your crimes...

389
00:24:08.914 --> 00:24:11.650
and dispense justice.

390
00:24:13.118 --> 00:24:14.185
Oh. dear.

391
00:24:14.186 --> 00:24:16.321
♪

392
00:24:27.265 --> 00:24:29.267
(muffled. echoing) No. no. no!

393
00:24:29.668 --> 00:24:32.870
I did as you asked. Your
Grace. I have been faithful.

394
00:24:32.871 --> 00:24:34.873
♪

395
00:24:44.015 --> 00:24:45.616
(music stops)

396
00:24:45.617 --> 00:24:47.786
(wind blowing)

397
00:24:53.492 --> 00:24:56.661
(unsettling music playing)

398
00:24:58.029 --> 00:25:00.131
(goat bleating)

399
00:25:11.610 --> 00:25:14.179
(person breathing heavily)

400
00:25:18.316 --> 00:25:20.652
(music fades out)

401
00:25:31.730 --> 00:25:33.832
(crown clinks)

402
00:25:48.013 --> 00:25:50.582
(Viserys breathing heavily)

403
00:25:52.350 --> 00:25:54.452
What is this?

404
00:25:56.221 --> 00:25:58.557
I never wanted it.

405
00:26:01.092 --> 00:26:03.428
I was right not to.

406
00:26:07.132 --> 00:26:09.901
All that pain it caused.

407
00:26:13.405 --> 00:26:16.775
It crushes whoever wears it.

408
00:26:20.612 --> 00:26:23.415
You always wanted it. Daemon.

409
00:26:28.787 --> 00:26:31.323
Do you want it still?

410
00:26:32.023 --> 00:26:34.593
(high-pitched ringing)

411
00:26:40.665 --> 00:26:43.602
- (Aegon grunting) - Grand
Maester Orwyle: Steady. Slowly.

412
00:26:46.738 --> 00:26:47.972
Aegon Targaryen: I can't.

413
00:26:47.973 --> 00:26:50.909
Orwyle: You can. You
must try. Your Grace.

414
00:26:52.377 --> 00:26:55.512
(Aegon groans)

415
00:26:55.513 --> 00:26:59.350
- (cane snaps. clatters)
- (Aegon wincing. yelling)

416
00:26:59.351 --> 00:27:01.619
I can't. I can't!

417
00:27:01.620 --> 00:27:03.421
(groaning)

418
00:27:06.157 --> 00:27:08.359
I'm sorry. Your Grace.
I'm sorry. Your Grace.

419
00:27:08.360 --> 00:27:11.862
- (cries) Oh. God. Oh. God.
- (knocking at door)

420
00:27:11.863 --> 00:27:13.030
- (Aegon yells)
- A moment!

421
00:27:13.031 --> 00:27:15.833
- (aggressive knocking)
- A moment. please!

422
00:27:15.834 --> 00:27:17.636
(door opens)

423
00:27:19.437 --> 00:27:23.107
You really oughtn't to be doing
that alone. Grand Maester.

424
00:27:23.108 --> 00:27:24.876
(groaning)

425
00:27:30.849 --> 00:27:32.182
Allow me.

426
00:27:32.183 --> 00:27:34.285
(Aegon panicking)

427
00:27:34.853 --> 00:27:36.521
Aegon: No. no. no.
no. no. no. no.

428
00:27:36.921 --> 00:27:38.690
Forgive me. Your Grace.

429
00:27:39.791 --> 00:27:42.127
(grunting. yelling)

430
00:27:50.168 --> 00:27:52.670
- Orwyle: Be careful.
- Wait. wait.

431
00:27:52.671 --> 00:27:54.472
(yelling)

432
00:28:00.278 --> 00:28:02.814
(Aegon breathing heavily)

433
00:28:03.281 --> 00:28:05.650
Your progress is impressive.

434
00:28:07.252 --> 00:28:11.256
But I'm afraid you
must work harder.

435
00:28:12.590 --> 00:28:14.692
Your strength will return.

436
00:28:14.693 --> 00:28:17.027
There are... adjustments

437
00:28:17.028 --> 00:28:18.595
to the gait and so forth

438
00:28:18.596 --> 00:28:21.533
that you will learn
now that you are...

439
00:28:22.567 --> 00:28:23.801
as you are.

440
00:28:23.802 --> 00:28:25.570
(grunting)

441
00:28:36.915 --> 00:28:39.050
You should be more cautious.

442
00:28:39.417 --> 00:28:41.719
I. I should. Lord Larys.

443
00:28:41.720 --> 00:28:44.321
He-He needs rest.
He should be abed.

444
00:28:44.322 --> 00:28:46.724
I push him on your instruction.

445
00:28:46.725 --> 00:28:49.194
I'll have the sentry
give you more warning.

446
00:28:51.596 --> 00:28:53.330
Let him try again
in a few hours.

447
00:28:53.331 --> 00:28:54.966
He is spent.

448
00:28:57.969 --> 00:29:00.705
(softly) It will be long
before he may rest again.

449
00:29:05.844 --> 00:29:07.545
(Aegon groans)

450
00:29:07.712 --> 00:29:09.814
(indistinct chatter)

451
00:29:13.118 --> 00:29:14.419
Corlys: Alyn.

452
00:29:17.388 --> 00:29:18.990
Alyn of Hull: My lord.

453
00:29:22.026 --> 00:29:24.729
Corlys: I have tasks that
need your personal attention.

454
00:29:25.096 --> 00:29:27.865
The queen requires ships at
her service in King's Landing.

455
00:29:27.866 --> 00:29:30.634
Charter fishing vessels.
Pay whatever they demand

456
00:29:30.635 --> 00:29:33.938
but ensure their
captains are dependable.

457
00:29:36.174 --> 00:29:38.509
- Put trusted swords aboard.
- Yes. m'lord.

458
00:29:38.510 --> 00:29:40.244
Have them wait just
outside the harbor.

459
00:29:40.245 --> 00:29:43.448
And there will be a message
to carry to one she will name.

460
00:29:50.155 --> 00:29:54.626
The queen has found a new
rider for one of her dragons.

461
00:29:55.126 --> 00:29:57.561
I've heard tell of it.

462
00:29:57.562 --> 00:29:59.030
The rider is your brother.

463
00:30:03.535 --> 00:30:06.037
She now makes the
call for others.

464
00:30:06.538 --> 00:30:08.705
Our people are of Old Valyria.

465
00:30:08.706 --> 00:30:12.377
but... we are no dragonlords.

466
00:30:13.845 --> 00:30:19.017
I confess. I knew little
of your mother's heritage.

467
00:30:21.486 --> 00:30:23.121
If it is...

468
00:30:24.155 --> 00:30:26.324
something in the blood.

469
00:30:31.029 --> 00:30:33.463
My brother was ever restless.

470
00:30:33.464 --> 00:30:36.367
yearning for some
sign of his worth.

471
00:30:37.669 --> 00:30:40.637
I am of salt and sea.

472
00:30:40.638 --> 00:30:43.141
I yearn for nothing else.

473
00:30:52.250 --> 00:30:54.151
{\an8}(wind blowing)

474
00:30:54.152 --> 00:30:57.589
{\an8}(tense. solemn music playing)

475
00:31:21.546 --> 00:31:23.615
♪

476
00:31:37.996 --> 00:31:41.399
(tense. mischievous
music playing)

477
00:31:51.776 --> 00:31:53.878
(wind blowing)

478
00:32:02.287 --> 00:32:03.988
(panting)

479
00:32:07.625 --> 00:32:09.727
♪

480
00:32:21.205 --> 00:32:23.508
(music fades out)

481
00:32:25.843 --> 00:32:28.613
(ambient nature sounds)

482
00:32:36.087 --> 00:32:38.189
(horse grunting)

483
00:32:44.329 --> 00:32:46.698
I will retire now. Ser Rickard.

484
00:32:53.838 --> 00:32:57.442
When does Your Grace mean
to return to the city?

485
00:32:59.210 --> 00:33:01.346
I'm not yet certain I do.

486
00:33:03.014 --> 00:33:04.148
Good night.

487
00:33:12.523 --> 00:33:15.726
Jacaerys Velaryon: The
lowborn claiming dragons.

488
00:33:15.727 --> 00:33:17.527
was it her idea?

489
00:33:17.528 --> 00:33:19.262
Lady Mysaria?

490
00:33:19.263 --> 00:33:22.666
You were enthusiastic enough
when Ser Steffon made his claim.

491
00:33:22.667 --> 00:33:24.801
He was the Lord Commander
of your Queensguard.

492
00:33:24.802 --> 00:33:27.371
Heir to the Dun Fort.
These people are...

493
00:33:27.372 --> 00:33:28.740
Courageous.

494
00:33:29.340 --> 00:33:31.042
Mongrels.

495
00:33:34.445 --> 00:33:36.180
(Rhaenyra sighs)

496
00:33:36.647 --> 00:33:37.915
Jace.

497
00:33:40.785 --> 00:33:42.652
Think what is at stake.

498
00:33:42.653 --> 00:33:45.890
I know well what is at stake.

499
00:33:47.692 --> 00:33:50.293
House Targaryen is the
blood of the dragon.

500
00:33:50.294 --> 00:33:53.131
If any may lay claim to
it. what are we then?

501
00:33:53.598 --> 00:33:56.501
The rightful rulers
of the Seven Kingdoms.

502
00:33:56.901 --> 00:34:00.570
And what if one of your baseborn.
silver-haired dragonriders

503
00:34:00.571 --> 00:34:03.373
decides he wants to
rule the Seven Kingdoms?

504
00:34:03.374 --> 00:34:06.810
Did the Conqueror's
dream foretell that?

505
00:34:06.811 --> 00:34:09.714
What else would you have me do?

506
00:34:11.416 --> 00:34:13.250
Prosecute a war.
which we will lose.

507
00:34:13.251 --> 00:34:15.886
in which thousands will die.

508
00:34:15.887 --> 00:34:17.854
Or fly against Vhagar myself?

509
00:34:17.855 --> 00:34:21.592
Or perhaps you will fly
against her on Vermax.

510
00:34:23.995 --> 00:34:28.866
Jace. with these riders.
we can end a needless war.

511
00:34:29.867 --> 00:34:32.469
I may take my rightful
place on my father's throne.

512
00:34:32.470 --> 00:34:34.539
Jacaerys: And when you die?

513
00:34:38.476 --> 00:34:40.812
(chuckles) You are my heir.

514
00:34:52.056 --> 00:34:54.424
(inhales)

515
00:34:54.425 --> 00:34:57.128
Did you think I
would have dark hair?

516
00:35:05.069 --> 00:35:07.537
When you took Harwin
Strong into your bed.

517
00:35:07.538 --> 00:35:08.905
did you think I might favor him.

518
00:35:08.906 --> 00:35:10.641
or did it not cross your mind?

519
00:35:13.111 --> 00:35:16.247
- Jacaerys...
- I'm no fool. Mother!

520
00:35:16.781 --> 00:35:19.183
The proof is here
for all to see.

521
00:35:21.719 --> 00:35:24.054
Yet I may argue my
legitimacy to succeed you

522
00:35:24.055 --> 00:35:26.257
because I have a dragon.

523
00:35:29.293 --> 00:35:31.762
And now you say you will
strip that from me too.

524
00:35:47.778 --> 00:35:50.615
I mislike all of
this. (sniffles)

525
00:35:52.517 --> 00:35:54.519
Then don't pursue it.

526
00:35:59.724 --> 00:36:02.626
(light music playing)

527
00:36:02.627 --> 00:36:06.429
But I cannot gainsay
that which the gods

528
00:36:06.430 --> 00:36:08.132
have laid before me.

529
00:36:15.873 --> 00:36:19.243
(light. tense music playing)

530
00:36:27.718 --> 00:36:30.855
(tense music playing)

531
00:36:33.324 --> 00:36:36.761
Do whatever you must to
see that it finds her.

532
00:36:42.200 --> 00:36:44.502
♪

533
00:36:49.740 --> 00:36:51.876
(indistinct chatter)

534
00:37:02.887 --> 00:37:04.622
From the queen.

535
00:37:05.590 --> 00:37:07.692
♪

536
00:37:09.894 --> 00:37:12.230
(singers vocalizing)

537
00:37:29.614 --> 00:37:32.550
♪

538
00:37:46.264 --> 00:37:48.332
♪

539
00:37:51.469 --> 00:37:53.103
Mujja: You won't believe this.

540
00:37:53.104 --> 00:37:54.904
(indistinct chatter)

541
00:37:54.905 --> 00:37:56.906
Word is. Rhaenyra's recruiting

542
00:37:56.907 --> 00:37:58.708
smallfolk to go to
(whispers) Dragonstone.

543
00:37:58.709 --> 00:38:01.578
- Oh. fuck that.
- Oh. they wouldn't take you anyway.

544
00:38:01.579 --> 00:38:03.813
(laughter)

545
00:38:03.814 --> 00:38:07.251
They're looking... for
Targaryen bastards.

546
00:38:08.185 --> 00:38:10.153
Boats leave tonight.
Hour of the bat.

547
00:38:10.154 --> 00:38:13.556
Seven hells. Ulf.
This is it! (laughs)

548
00:38:13.557 --> 00:38:15.292
Yeah. a likely story.

549
00:38:15.293 --> 00:38:17.427
- You've been taken in. lads.
- Mujja: No. no. no. no. no.

550
00:38:17.428 --> 00:38:20.263
The queen's own handmaid is
here. spreadin' the word.

551
00:38:20.264 --> 00:38:21.831
Ulf: Well. that's a shame
'cause I'd have been

552
00:38:21.832 --> 00:38:24.601
first in line if it
wasn't for my injury.

553
00:38:24.602 --> 00:38:26.903
- 'Cause my leg hasn't been the same since...
- Are you touched?

554
00:38:26.904 --> 00:38:28.972
He's saying you
can claim a dragon.

555
00:38:28.973 --> 00:38:31.474
The barkeep from the
Seven Maesters is goin'.

556
00:38:31.475 --> 00:38:33.009
And two of the
girls from Mother's.

557
00:38:33.010 --> 00:38:35.945
- (hushed) A chance to stick it to Aemond.
- And claim a dragon.

558
00:38:35.946 --> 00:38:38.081
- (hushed) Dragon!
- Yeah. no. I know.

559
00:38:38.082 --> 00:38:41.651
- Mujja: What?
- I know. I just... I can't...

560
00:38:41.652 --> 00:38:44.121
I can't be sure it's all true.

561
00:38:47.391 --> 00:38:50.760
You can't mean that
you've been drinkin'

562
00:38:50.761 --> 00:38:53.196
at the expense of all
these. these good people

563
00:38:53.197 --> 00:38:55.365
- for a fiction? No. Ulf.
- No. no. Shh.

564
00:38:55.366 --> 00:38:57.133
All spark and no tinder?

565
00:38:57.134 --> 00:38:58.868
- Mujja: They won't be happy.
- Cley: They'll be very unhappy.

566
00:38:58.869 --> 00:39:01.004
- Never live it down.
- Never live it down.

567
00:39:01.005 --> 00:39:03.440
- Come on. Ulf. the time has come!
- Mujja: Come on!

568
00:39:03.441 --> 00:39:04.974
Cley: Can I see
a little glimmer?

569
00:39:04.975 --> 00:39:07.510
- Mujja: Where is it?
- There's the Ulf I know.

570
00:39:07.511 --> 00:39:09.579
Mujja: Yes! Yes. there he is!

571
00:39:09.580 --> 00:39:13.316
- Yes. yes!
- Wine! Wine for Ulf the Dragonlord!

572
00:39:13.317 --> 00:39:15.552
- Ulf the Dragonlord!
- (all cheering)

573
00:39:15.553 --> 00:39:19.489
Ulf the Dragonlord!
Ulf the Dragonlord!

574
00:39:19.490 --> 00:39:21.892
(all chanting "Ulf")

575
00:39:25.563 --> 00:39:27.163
(Cley laughs)

576
00:39:27.164 --> 00:39:29.333
(fire crackling)

577
00:39:30.701 --> 00:39:33.236
Kat: I don't want you to go.

578
00:39:33.237 --> 00:39:35.004
I have to. Kat.

579
00:39:35.005 --> 00:39:36.873
We'll go to my
brother in Tumbleton.

580
00:39:36.874 --> 00:39:39.409
They'll have food.
You'll find work.

581
00:39:39.410 --> 00:39:41.211
I can't ignore this.

582
00:39:41.212 --> 00:39:43.848
(dog barking outside)

583
00:39:45.649 --> 00:39:47.418
I never knew my father.

584
00:39:49.820 --> 00:39:51.922
That much is true.

585
00:39:56.127 --> 00:39:58.262
But I did know my mother.

586
00:40:01.866 --> 00:40:03.968
(outside chatter)

587
00:40:10.775 --> 00:40:13.343
I hid it from you.

588
00:40:13.344 --> 00:40:15.579
And I'm sorry for that.

589
00:40:16.814 --> 00:40:18.282
(sighs)

590
00:40:19.450 --> 00:40:21.152
She worked...

591
00:40:22.319 --> 00:40:23.654
in a pleasure house.

592
00:40:25.156 --> 00:40:27.824
She was granted more
freedom than most

593
00:40:27.825 --> 00:40:30.494
because of who she was.

594
00:40:32.830 --> 00:40:36.167
And because rich men paid more
to fuck a woman with silver hair.

595
00:40:40.638 --> 00:40:42.606
She used to tell me...

596
00:40:43.707 --> 00:40:47.144
I was no different
to her brother's boys

597
00:40:49.180 --> 00:40:52.316
Viserys... and Daemon.

598
00:40:55.653 --> 00:40:57.521
(Hugh inhales)

599
00:40:57.988 --> 00:41:00.157
But I was ashamed of her.

600
00:41:02.993 --> 00:41:06.197
I tried to make my
way with my own hands.

601
00:41:07.798 --> 00:41:10.767
(solemn music playing)

602
00:41:10.768 --> 00:41:13.137
I could not protect you.

603
00:41:13.704 --> 00:41:16.807
I could not keep our girl alive.

604
00:41:24.381 --> 00:41:25.683
And now...

605
00:41:27.351 --> 00:41:30.954
we would never want again.

606
00:41:30.955 --> 00:41:33.557
If I claimed a dragon...

607
00:41:34.758 --> 00:41:36.793
they'd make you a lady.

608
00:41:36.794 --> 00:41:38.963
♪

609
00:41:42.299 --> 00:41:45.135
I do not care to
be a lady. Hugh.

610
00:41:47.905 --> 00:41:50.508
And neither do I
want to be a widow.

611
00:41:52.276 --> 00:41:54.345
♪

612
00:41:58.082 --> 00:42:00.651
I have to do somethin'.

613
00:42:01.452 --> 00:42:04.588
(tense music playing)

614
00:42:16.033 --> 00:42:18.102
♪

615
00:42:27.444 --> 00:42:31.282
- (music fades out)
- (ambient nature sounds)

616
00:42:31.982 --> 00:42:35.119
(light music playing)

617
00:42:51.835 --> 00:42:53.938
(wind blowing)

618
00:42:57.007 --> 00:42:59.076
♪

619
00:43:20.898 --> 00:43:22.967
♪

620
00:43:51.295 --> 00:43:54.431
♪

621
00:44:15.285 --> 00:44:17.388
(music intensifies)

622
00:44:37.841 --> 00:44:39.576
(music fades out)

623
00:44:40.010 --> 00:44:42.413
{\an8}(dragonkeeper speaking
High Valyrian)

624
00:44:43.547 --> 00:44:45.683
{\an8}(speaking High Valyrian)

625
00:45:35.899 --> 00:45:38.235
(nearby dragon growls)

626
00:45:39.002 --> 00:45:41.105
(deep breath)

627
00:46:00.758 --> 00:46:05.095
I used to think I knew what it
was to claim a dragon. but...

628
00:46:09.566 --> 00:46:12.169
I understand now that what
I thought I knew is...

629
00:46:12.970 --> 00:46:14.772
ash in the wind.

630
00:46:27.184 --> 00:46:29.585
Perhaps it is blood.

631
00:46:29.586 --> 00:46:31.921
Or worth.

632
00:46:31.922 --> 00:46:34.358
Or perhaps it's something else.

633
00:46:38.729 --> 00:46:44.701
Each of you... has left behind
a life to answer this call.

634
00:46:45.836 --> 00:46:50.874
A life to which... you
might never return.

635
00:46:52.643 --> 00:46:55.813
If you survive. you
will be transformed.

636
00:46:56.880 --> 00:47:00.984
No man or woman can face
a dragon and be otherwise.

637
00:47:06.456 --> 00:47:10.092
Some of you may welcome
the prospect of change.

638
00:47:10.093 --> 00:47:13.931
even death. given
the alternatives:

639
00:47:14.264 --> 00:47:18.635
privation... starvation. war.

640
00:47:19.503 --> 00:47:21.904
This is our purpose.

641
00:47:21.905 --> 00:47:24.341
to end those hardships.

642
00:47:26.076 --> 00:47:27.578
For you...

643
00:47:28.912 --> 00:47:32.382
for your kin. for all the realm.

644
00:47:33.417 --> 00:47:37.587
With these two dragons
added to our number.

645
00:47:37.588 --> 00:47:40.524
the enemy will have no
choice but to give way.

646
00:47:41.859 --> 00:47:44.661
And peace will be restored...

647
00:47:46.897 --> 00:47:50.499
suffering will be ended.

648
00:47:50.500 --> 00:47:53.370
and without bloodshed...

649
00:47:54.438 --> 00:47:56.540
gods willing.

650
00:47:57.975 --> 00:48:00.344
(nearby dragon growls)

651
00:48:05.582 --> 00:48:09.853
- (tense music playing)
- (deep breath)

652
00:48:11.355 --> 00:48:13.522
The dragon

653
00:48:13.523 --> 00:48:15.726
named Vermithor...

654
00:48:17.060 --> 00:48:20.596
is the largest in the
world after Vhagar.

655
00:48:20.597 --> 00:48:24.468
and... perhaps.
the most fierce.

656
00:48:28.572 --> 00:48:30.840
He's called the Bronze Fury.

657
00:48:30.841 --> 00:48:32.976
♪

658
00:48:36.980 --> 00:48:38.749
We'll go to him now.

659
00:48:40.851 --> 00:48:42.119
And...

660
00:48:45.522 --> 00:48:47.291
may the gods bless you.

661
00:48:52.062 --> 00:48:54.131
♪

662
00:49:15.085 --> 00:49:17.421
(music fades out)

663
00:49:26.463 --> 00:49:28.865
{\an8}(Rhaenyra speaking
High Valyrian)

664
00:49:38.608 --> 00:49:41.077
(heavy footstep)

665
00:49:41.078 --> 00:49:42.846
(rumbling)

666
00:49:58.161 --> 00:50:00.297
(heavy footsteps)

667
00:50:16.847 --> 00:50:18.982
(Vermithor roars)

668
00:50:30.627 --> 00:50:32.829
{\an8}(Rhaenyra speaking
High Valyrian)

669
00:50:33.530 --> 00:50:35.165
(screeches)

670
00:50:36.933 --> 00:50:39.069
(Vermithor grumbling)

671
00:50:59.156 --> 00:51:01.258
(Vermithor calms)

672
00:51:06.396 --> 00:51:08.098
(grumbling)

673
00:51:42.666 --> 00:51:44.968
(Vermithor growling)

674
00:51:49.506 --> 00:51:51.775
Who among you would be first?

675
00:51:53.043 --> 00:51:55.145
(all murmuring)

676
00:52:02.018 --> 00:52:04.154
(Vermithor grumbles)

677
00:52:08.325 --> 00:52:10.026
(grumbling)

678
00:52:21.471 --> 00:52:23.439
I have nothing more to tell you.

679
00:52:23.440 --> 00:52:26.143
It must be the
dragon who speaks.

680
00:52:33.216 --> 00:52:35.318
(all murmuring)

681
00:52:48.165 --> 00:52:50.300
(Vermithor grumbling)

682
00:53:16.826 --> 00:53:18.662
(all panicking)

683
00:53:18.895 --> 00:53:22.399
(deep. low growling)

684
00:53:37.314 --> 00:53:39.416
(Vermithor calms)

685
00:53:43.587 --> 00:53:45.288
(panting)

686
00:53:50.694 --> 00:53:51.860
(roars)

687
00:53:51.861 --> 00:53:54.030
(all screaming)

688
00:54:00.503 --> 00:54:03.106
- Your Grace. we must away!
- No.

689
00:54:06.776 --> 00:54:08.478
(screaming)

690
00:54:13.717 --> 00:54:14.784
(grunts)

691
00:54:15.652 --> 00:54:17.387
(screaming)

692
00:54:21.024 --> 00:54:22.292
(grunts)

693
00:54:25.528 --> 00:54:27.230
(screaming)

694
00:54:31.601 --> 00:54:32.902
(roars)

695
00:54:38.808 --> 00:54:40.977
dragonseed: Help me! Help...

696
00:54:41.544 --> 00:54:42.812
Help me!

697
00:54:45.515 --> 00:54:48.918
(tense. solemn music playing)

698
00:55:05.635 --> 00:55:07.704
♪

699
00:55:13.843 --> 00:55:15.979
(Vermithor screeches)

700
00:55:21.885 --> 00:55:23.520
(coughing)

701
00:55:23.920 --> 00:55:27.123
- (Vermithor roars)
- (panting)

702
00:55:30.327 --> 00:55:31.628
Oh. f...

703
00:55:34.564 --> 00:55:37.701
(tense music playing)

704
00:55:41.137 --> 00:55:44.473
- (indistinct yelling)
- (Vermithor screeches)

705
00:55:44.474 --> 00:55:46.242
(panting)

706
00:55:49.946 --> 00:55:52.082
(smallfolk screaming)

707
00:55:53.883 --> 00:55:56.919
- (Hugh panting)
- (smallfolk yelling)

708
00:55:56.920 --> 00:55:59.556
(Vermithor screeches. roars)

709
00:56:00.657 --> 00:56:01.925
(screams)

710
00:56:02.592 --> 00:56:03.860
(grunts)

711
00:56:04.694 --> 00:56:06.830
(smallfolk screaming)

712
00:56:10.500 --> 00:56:12.501
- No!
- Shh. shh. shh!

713
00:56:12.502 --> 00:56:14.671
(both panting)

714
00:56:17.640 --> 00:56:19.776
(smallfolk screaming)

715
00:56:21.778 --> 00:56:22.911
(roars)

716
00:56:22.912 --> 00:56:24.714
(screaming)

717
00:56:31.621 --> 00:56:32.788
(roars)

718
00:56:32.789 --> 00:56:34.557
(panting)

719
00:56:35.258 --> 00:56:37.394
(smallfolk screaming)

720
00:56:38.328 --> 00:56:40.430
(heavy footsteps)

721
00:56:41.531 --> 00:56:43.633
(Vermithor grumbles)

722
00:56:46.069 --> 00:56:47.771
(screeches)

723
00:56:52.275 --> 00:56:53.977
(roaring)

724
00:56:57.647 --> 00:56:58.915
(grunts)

725
00:57:03.086 --> 00:57:04.788
(grumbling)

726
00:57:07.857 --> 00:57:09.125
(groans)

727
00:57:10.026 --> 00:57:12.528
(smallfolk panicking)

728
00:57:12.529 --> 00:57:15.597
Here! Here I am!

729
00:57:15.598 --> 00:57:17.400
(roaring)

730
00:57:28.445 --> 00:57:29.845
I'm ready.

731
00:57:29.846 --> 00:57:31.614
(roaring)

732
00:57:45.428 --> 00:57:49.031
(yells) Come on!

733
00:57:49.032 --> 00:57:51.066
(heavy breathing)

734
00:57:51.067 --> 00:57:53.269
(Vermithor grumbling)

735
00:58:08.585 --> 00:58:10.687
(Vermithor calms)

736
00:58:26.936 --> 00:58:29.005
♪

737
00:58:47.257 --> 00:58:49.291
(music intensifies)

738
00:58:49.292 --> 00:58:51.861
♪

739
00:59:02.672 --> 00:59:04.840
(music fades out)

740
00:59:04.841 --> 00:59:08.044
(Ulf panting. grunts)

741
00:59:28.965 --> 00:59:31.033
(grunting)

742
00:59:31.034 --> 00:59:32.802
(coughing)

743
00:59:34.604 --> 00:59:36.940
(groans. panting)

744
00:59:37.907 --> 00:59:39.208
(coughs)

745
00:59:45.782 --> 00:59:47.483
(panting)

746
00:59:53.289 --> 00:59:55.391
(dragon growls)

747
01:00:02.732 --> 01:00:04.834
(heavy breathing)

748
01:00:06.903 --> 01:00:09.005
(dragon grumbling)

749
01:00:21.985 --> 01:00:24.988
- (roars)
- (heavy footsteps)

750
01:00:29.258 --> 01:00:30.960
(grumbles)

751
01:00:34.564 --> 01:00:36.866
(Ulf grunting)

752
01:00:44.874 --> 01:00:46.609
(grumbling)

753
01:01:03.292 --> 01:01:05.395
(Silverwing calms)

754
01:01:10.466 --> 01:01:12.067
(panting)

755
01:01:12.068 --> 01:01:13.836
(grunting)

756
01:01:14.804 --> 01:01:16.506
(grumbles)

757
01:01:29.986 --> 01:01:31.453
(exhales)

758
01:01:31.454 --> 01:01:33.222
(laughing)

759
01:01:34.490 --> 01:01:38.960
"Lord Ormund Hightower
makes slow progress.

760
01:01:38.961 --> 01:01:41.329
"There is great
concern that his host

761
01:01:41.330 --> 01:01:42.497
"is threatened on two fronts

762
01:01:42.498 --> 01:01:46.068
by armies allied
with House Beesbury."

763
01:01:46.069 --> 01:01:48.537
(outside chatter)

764
01:01:48.538 --> 01:01:50.906
However. in happier tidings.

765
01:01:50.907 --> 01:01:52.607
Prince Daeron's
dragon. Tessarion.

766
01:01:52.608 --> 01:01:54.342
has at last taken to wing.

767
01:01:54.343 --> 01:01:56.912
Your brother expects
to join the fight soon.

768
01:01:56.913 --> 01:01:59.048
Guard (shouts): Dragon!

769
01:01:59.348 --> 01:02:00.916
Ironrod: And when he does.

770
01:02:00.917 --> 01:02:03.552
the Hightower host
will be unstoppable.

771
01:02:03.553 --> 01:02:06.655
Guard (shouts):
Dragon! Inside! Now!

772
01:02:06.656 --> 01:02:10.093
(indistinct shouting outside)

773
01:02:14.630 --> 01:02:17.632
(tense music playing)

774
01:02:17.633 --> 01:02:19.802
(bells ringing)

775
01:02:21.003 --> 01:02:23.038
guard (shouts):
Take positions!

776
01:02:23.039 --> 01:02:25.340
(guards shouting)

777
01:02:25.341 --> 01:02:28.009
♪

778
01:02:28.010 --> 01:02:30.213
(Silverwing calling)

779
01:02:34.317 --> 01:02:36.419
(yelling)

780
01:02:39.589 --> 01:02:42.759
(yelling. laughing)

781
01:02:57.907 --> 01:03:00.208
♪

782
01:03:00.209 --> 01:03:01.943
- (Aemond grunts)
- (horse neighs)

783
01:03:01.944 --> 01:03:03.578
Open the gates!

784
01:03:03.579 --> 01:03:07.250
(chattering. shouting)

785
01:03:19.495 --> 01:03:21.831
(music fades out)

786
01:03:23.399 --> 01:03:26.536
(intense music playing)

787
01:03:27.470 --> 01:03:28.771
(roars)

788
01:03:41.017 --> 01:03:43.119
♪

789
01:03:47.623 --> 01:03:48.891
(roars)

790
01:03:51.093 --> 01:03:53.496
{\an8}(speaking High Valyrian)

791
01:03:56.399 --> 01:03:57.667
